page.title: 10The skies above our heads(3)
page.content: As well as the heavy military and civ ilian aircraft presence over the block, light planes are also seen in great numbers.They usually travel at about 3000 feet,and are using the area because of its good central position giving good N.E. to S.W. access avoiding Birmingham and London. Let's not forget the birds.These are our Top 20 most common birds:starling, house sparrow,blackbird,song thrush,wood pigeon,carrion crow,rook,jackdaw,yellowhammer,magpie, collared dove,pheasant,swallow,moorhen blue tit,lapwing,house martin,stock- dove,coot and swift. Often heard but not seen are cuckoo,jay and green woodpecker.Other more unusual birds seen in our block are tawny owl, sparrowhawk,kestrel,little owl and Canada goose( on Leam Pool).
